.TH UTILITYKIT 1 "July 2026" "UtilityKit v5.10.6" "UtilityKit Tools"
.SH NAME
utility-yt_download \- Interactive YouTube (and supported site) video/audio downloader wrapping `yt-dlp`.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B utility yt_download
[\fIoptions\fP]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Interactive YouTube (and supported site) video/audio downloader wrapping `yt-dlp`.
.SH FEATURES
.PP
.IP \(bu 4
\fBFull format listing\fP — runs \fCyt-dlp -F\fP and shows every available format code
.IP \(bu 4
\fBFlexible format selection\fP — enter any format specifier (\fC137+140\fP, \fCbv*+ba/b\fP, \fCbest\fP, etc.)
.IP \(bu 4
\fBAudio extraction\fP — download audio-only in mp3, m4a, opus, flac, or aac
.IP \(bu 4
\fBSubtitles\fP — auto-download and embed all available subtitle tracks
.IP \(bu 4
\fBThumbnails & metadata\fP — embed into the file for rich player support
.IP \(bu 4
\fBPlaylist support\fP — toggle between single video and full playlist download
.IP \(bu 4
\fBCustom output\fP — choose directory and filename template
.IP \(bu 4
\fBCLI subcommands\fP — \fClist\fP, \fCinfo\fP, \fCaudio\fP, \fCdownload\fP for scripting
.IP \(bu 4
\fBStandalone\fP — works as \fCbash _yt_download.sh\fP or via \fCmain.sh ytdl\fP
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH INTERACTIVE WIZARD
.PP
.EX
bash _yt_download.sh
.EE
or through the hub:
.EX
bash main.sh ytdl
.EE
.PP
The wizard walks through:
.IP \(em 4
URL input
.IP \(em 4
Fetches title, channel, duration
.IP \(em 4
Displays full format table
.IP \(em 4
Prompts for format code(s)
.IP \(em 4
Asks about audio-only, subtitles, thumbnails, metadata, playlist
.IP \(em 4
Output directory + filename template
.IP \(em 4
Summary & confirmation → download
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH CLI SUBCOMMANDS
.PP
.EX
bash main.sh ytdl list https://youtube.com/watch?v=...

bash main.sh ytdl info https://youtube.com/watch?v=...

bash main.sh ytdl audio https://youtube.com/watch?v=...

bash main.sh ytdl audio https://youtube.com/watch?v=... --audio-format opus

bash main.sh ytdl download https://youtube.com/watch?v=... \
  --format 137+140 \
  --subs \
  --output ~/Videos
.EE
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH DOWNLOAD OPTIONS
.PP
Option   |   Default   |   Description
\fC--format CODE\fP   |   \fCbv*+ba/b\fP   |   Format specifier (from \fClist\fP output)
\fC--audio-only\fP   |   off   |   Extract audio stream only
\fC--audio-format FMT\fP   |   \fCmp3\fP   |   Audio codec: mp3, m4a, opus, flac, aac
\fC--subs\fP   |   off   |   Embed all available subtitles
\fC--no-thumb\fP   |   off   |   Skip embedding thumbnail
\fC--no-meta\fP   |   off   |   Skip embedding metadata
\fC--playlist\fP   |   off   |   Download all items in a playlist
\fC--output DIR\fP   |   \fC~/Downloads/YouTube\fP   |   Custom output directory
\fC-h, --help\fP   |   —   |   Show help
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH FORMAT SPECIFIER EXAMPLES
.PP
Value   |   What it does
\fCbest\fP   |   Best single-file combined stream
\fCbv*+ba/b\fP   |   Best video + best audio, merge; fallback to combined
\fC137+140\fP   |   1080p h264 video + medium m4a audio
\fC137\fP   |   1080p video only (no audio stream)
\fCbestvideo+bestaudio\fP   |   Explicit best of each, will merge
\fCworst\fP   |   Lowest quality
.PP
See yt-dlp format selection docs] for all options.
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH REQUIREMENTS
.PP
.IP \(bu 4
\fByt-dlp\fP — install via:
  ```bash
  pip install yt-dlp
  brew install yt-dlp       # macOS
  sudo apt install yt-dlp   # Debian/Ubuntu
  ```
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH EXIT CODES
.PP
Code   |   Meaning
\fC0\fP   |   Success or cancelled by user
\fC1\fP   |   Missing \fCyt-dlp\fP or download failure
